In this paper, we prove sharp estimates and existence results for anisotropic
nonlinear elliptic problems with lower order terms depending on the gradient.
Our prototype is:
  $ \left\{ \begin{array}{ll} -\mathcal Q_{p}u =[H(Du)]^{q}+f(x) &\text{in
}\Omega,\\ u=0&\text{on }\partial\Omega. \end{array} \right. $
  Here $\Omega$ is a bounded open set of $\mathbb R^{N}$, $N\ge 2$, $0<p-1<q\le
p<N$, and $\mathcal Q_{p}$ is the anisotropic operator $ \mathcal Q_{p} u ={\rm
div}\left( [H(Du)]^{p-1}H_{\xi}(Du) \right)$, where $H$ is a suitable norm of
$\mathbb R^{N}$. Moreover, $f$ belongs to an appropriate Marcinkiewicz space.